WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:14.342 align:middle line:10%
[BACKGROUND MUSIC]

00:00:14.342 --> 00:00:15.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, and welcome.

00:00:15.550 --> 00:00:16.860 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:16.860 --> 00:00:19.020 align:middle line:84%
So when you try to
break an old habit,

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:22.050 align:middle line:84%
do you ever wonder why
it's so difficult to break?

00:00:22.050 --> 00:00:24.890 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to learn how to
be more positive and more

00:00:24.890 --> 00:00:27.620 align:middle line:84%
resilient, but you just
don't know how to do that?

00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:29.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, what if you saw
what it physically

00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:33.570 align:middle line:84%
looks like in the brain to be
stuck in a specific pattern,

00:00:33.570 --> 00:00:36.090 align:middle line:84%
or even better, what it
looks like in the brain

00:00:36.090 --> 00:00:40.740 align:middle line:84%
to be able to create new
patterns and to create change?

00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:42.422 align:middle line:90%
Joining me is Dr. Joe Dispenza.

00:00:42.422 --> 00:00:43.380 align:middle line:90%
He is a neuroscientist.

00:00:43.380 --> 00:00:45.990 align:middle line:84%
He was one of the visionaries
featured on the movie,

00:00:45.990 --> 00:00:47.300 align:middle line:90%
"What the Bleep Do We Know?"

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:48.750 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:00:48.750 --> 00:00:49.910 align:middle line:84%
>>JOE DISPENZA: Happy
to be with you, Lisa.

00:00:49.910 --> 00:00:50.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great to be with you.

00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:52.370 align:middle line:84%
We are in for such
a treat today.

00:00:52.370 --> 00:00:53.286 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Thank you.

00:00:53.286 --> 00:00:54.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So I want
to ask you, why

00:00:54.810 --> 00:00:57.215 align:middle line:84%
is it so darn
difficult to change?

00:00:57.215 --> 00:00:57.820 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:00:57.820 --> 00:00:59.029 align:middle line:90%
Why is change so difficult?

00:00:59.029 --> 00:01:01.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: That seems to
be the biggest question

00:01:01.070 --> 00:01:02.111 align:middle line:90%
that people want to know.

00:01:02.111 --> 00:01:04.360 align:middle line:90%
And let's define what change is.

00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:07.300 align:middle line:84%
Change is to be greater
than your environment,

00:01:07.300 --> 00:01:08.590 align:middle line:90%
to be greater than your body.

00:01:08.590 --> 00:01:09.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What does that mean?

00:01:09.420 --> 00:01:11.169 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Yeah, to
be greater than time.

00:01:11.169 --> 00:01:14.970 align:middle line:84%
So let's just say that
you wake up in the morning

00:01:14.970 --> 00:01:17.600 align:middle line:84%
and you do the same things
and you see the same people

00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:19.950 align:middle line:84%
and you go to the same places
and you drink coffee out

00:01:19.950 --> 00:01:22.859 align:middle line:84%
of your same mug, and you
drive to work the same way

00:01:22.859 --> 00:01:24.400 align:middle line:84%
and you see the same
people that push

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:26.020 align:middle line:90%
the same emotional buttons.

00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:29.000 align:middle line:84%
We could say that it's
the external environment,

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:30.770 align:middle line:84%
the outer world, all
the people you know

00:01:30.770 --> 00:01:33.500 align:middle line:84%
and the things that you do
and the places that you go.

00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:36.460 align:middle line:84%
Your external environment is
turning on different circuits

00:01:36.460 --> 00:01:40.440 align:middle line:84%
in your brain causing you to
consciously or unconsciously

00:01:40.440 --> 00:01:43.560 align:middle line:84%
think equal to
everything that you know.

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.990 align:middle line:84%
And as long as you react and
think equal to everything

00:01:45.990 --> 00:01:49.230 align:middle line:84%
you know, you keep creating
more of the same life.

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:50.880 align:middle line:84%
The principle in
neuroscience says

00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:54.130 align:middle line:84%
that nerve cells that fire
together, wire together.

00:01:54.130 --> 00:01:56.310 align:middle line:84%
So if you keep thinking
the same thoughts,

00:01:56.310 --> 00:01:58.790 align:middle line:84%
if you keep performing
the same actions,

00:01:58.790 --> 00:02:01.610 align:middle line:84%
if you keep living
by the same emotions,

00:02:01.610 --> 00:02:04.120 align:middle line:84%
over time the redundancy
of that begins

00:02:04.120 --> 00:02:07.260 align:middle line:84%
to hardwire the brain into
very specific patterns.

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:10.180 align:middle line:84%
And that pattern, then,
becomes our identity

00:02:10.180 --> 00:02:11.360 align:middle line:90%
or our personality.

00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:12.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There are some
visuals that we're

00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:14.278 align:middle line:84%
going to show in a
little bit that really

00:02:14.278 --> 00:02:15.910 align:middle line:90%
made such a huge impact on me.

00:02:15.910 --> 00:02:18.760 align:middle line:84%
So now, nerves that fire
together, wire together.

00:02:18.760 --> 00:02:20.930 align:middle line:84%
So the actual
nerves, the neurons

00:02:20.930 --> 00:02:24.060 align:middle line:84%
in the brain that create
synapses together,

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:25.062 align:middle line:90%
mend together?

00:02:25.062 --> 00:02:26.020 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Absolutely.

00:02:26.020 --> 00:02:27.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's
what a memory is?

00:02:27.830 --> 00:02:28.720 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Exactly.

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:30.860 align:middle line:84%
Learning is making new
synaptic connections,

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:32.290 align:middle line:90%
as we'll see in a minute.

00:02:32.290 --> 00:02:34.460 align:middle line:84%
And remembering is
maintaining and sustaining

00:02:34.460 --> 00:02:35.650 align:middle line:90%
those connections.

00:02:35.650 --> 00:02:38.790 align:middle line:84%
So most people, at a
certain point in their life,

00:02:38.790 --> 00:02:41.040 align:middle line:90%
they keep thinking the same way.

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:43.460 align:middle line:84%
They hardwire their brain
into a certain pattern.

00:02:43.460 --> 00:02:45.290 align:middle line:84%
They keep doing the
same things that

00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:48.280 align:middle line:84%
create habits that become
part of their identity.

00:02:48.280 --> 00:02:50.470 align:middle line:84%
And they keep living by
the same emotions that

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:52.720 align:middle line:84%
are created from the
same experiences.

00:02:52.720 --> 00:02:55.100 align:middle line:84%
And the redundancy
and repetition of that

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:58.560 align:middle line:84%
begins to cause the brain to
fire in very finite networks.

00:02:58.560 --> 00:03:00.820 align:middle line:84%
And that becomes what
we call our identity.

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:03.600 align:middle line:84%
So then by the time
we're 35 years old,

00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:06.760 align:middle line:84%
psychology says that,
for the most part,

00:03:06.760 --> 00:03:08.530 align:middle line:84%
we're a set of
memorized behaviors

00:03:08.530 --> 00:03:10.820 align:middle line:84%
and emotional
reactions that make up

00:03:10.820 --> 00:03:12.930 align:middle line:90%
who we are as an identity.

00:03:12.930 --> 00:03:15.650 align:middle line:84%
So when it comes time
to change, and people

00:03:15.650 --> 00:03:19.010 align:middle line:84%
have to realize that 5%
of their conscious mind

00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:21.870 align:middle line:84%
is working against
95% of what they've

00:03:21.870 --> 00:03:23.150 align:middle line:90%
memorized subconsciously.

00:03:23.150 --> 00:03:23.710 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:03:23.710 --> 00:03:25.709 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So that's
kind of like mind and body

00:03:25.709 --> 00:03:27.570 align:middle line:84%
working in opposition,
So that becomes

00:03:27.570 --> 00:03:30.090 align:middle line:84%
very difficult to
change because we're

00:03:30.090 --> 00:03:32.190 align:middle line:84%
using a very small
percentage to go against what

00:03:32.190 --> 00:03:34.280 align:middle line:90%
we've subconsciously memorized.

00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:36.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So when we
might think of something

00:03:36.480 --> 00:03:38.000 align:middle line:84%
that we want to
change in our lives

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:41.310 align:middle line:84%
or we maybe have a new idea
or read a book and say,

00:03:41.310 --> 00:03:43.200 align:middle line:90%
I really want to be like that.

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:45.330 align:middle line:84%
But then you go back
into the same pattern

00:03:45.330 --> 00:03:50.010 align:middle line:84%
and the same habits, it's
nearly impossible to change.

00:03:50.010 --> 00:03:51.470 align:middle line:84%
Unless you know
something about it.

00:03:51.470 --> 00:03:53.250 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
there's a new science

00:03:53.250 --> 00:03:55.740 align:middle line:90%
emerging called neuroplasticity.

00:03:55.740 --> 00:03:58.030 align:middle line:84%
And neuroplasticity
says that you're

00:03:58.030 --> 00:04:01.200 align:middle line:84%
in fact changed biologically
by every thought you think.

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:04.630 align:middle line:84%
Every new thing you learn, every
new experience that you create,

00:04:04.630 --> 00:04:08.250 align:middle line:84%
every new choice that you make,
every new dream that you dream,

00:04:08.250 --> 00:04:11.615 align:middle line:84%
your brain begins to fire in
new sequences and new patterns

00:04:11.615 --> 00:04:12.870 align:middle line:90%
and new combinations.

00:04:12.870 --> 00:04:15.220 align:middle line:84%
And whenever you make the
brain work differently,

00:04:15.220 --> 00:04:17.010 align:middle line:84%
you're changing your
mind because mind

00:04:17.010 --> 00:04:18.370 align:middle line:90%
is the brain in action.

00:04:18.370 --> 00:04:21.380 align:middle line:84%
So most people then, at a
certain point in their life,

00:04:21.380 --> 00:04:23.970 align:middle line:84%
they stop learning and
they start feeling.

00:04:23.970 --> 00:04:26.470 align:middle line:84%
And when feelings become
the barometer for change,

00:04:26.470 --> 00:04:28.520 align:middle line:84%
we'll always talk
ourselves out of greatness.

00:04:28.520 --> 00:04:30.379 align:middle line:84%
Because when you
change, it means

00:04:30.379 --> 00:04:31.920 align:middle line:84%
that you're going
to have to come out

00:04:31.920 --> 00:04:34.031 align:middle line:84%
of your resting
state, number one.

00:04:34.031 --> 00:04:35.530 align:middle line:84%
And number two,
you're going to have

00:04:35.530 --> 00:04:37.260 align:middle line:90%
to feel a little uncomfortable.

00:04:37.260 --> 00:04:39.820 align:middle line:84%
So the moment we start to
feel uncomfortable most people

00:04:39.820 --> 00:04:43.520 align:middle line:84%
go, ooh, I want to return back
to that familiar identity.

00:04:43.520 --> 00:04:45.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Even if it's painful.

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:45.863 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Exactly.

00:04:45.863 --> 00:04:48.000 align:middle line:84%
So here's how it
works physiologically.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:50.330 align:middle line:10%
If you have a thought, every
time you have a thought,

00:04:50.330 --> 00:04:51.960 align:middle line:10%
you make a chemical
in your brain.

00:04:51.960 --> 00:04:54.730 align:middle line:10%
If you have a great thought
or an unlimited thought,

00:04:54.730 --> 00:04:56.780 align:middle line:10%
you turn on a set of
circuits in your brain

00:04:56.780 --> 00:04:59.150 align:middle line:10%
in a very specific
sequence and pattern

00:04:59.150 --> 00:05:00.970 align:middle line:10%
that produces a
level of mind that

00:05:00.970 --> 00:05:03.370 align:middle line:10%
signals another part
of your brain for you

00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:06.410 align:middle line:10%
to begin to feel exactly the
way you were just thinking,

00:05:06.410 --> 00:05:07.410 align:middle line:10%
great or unlimited.

00:05:07.410 --> 00:05:10.020 align:middle line:84%
If you have a negative
thought or an unhappy thought,

00:05:10.020 --> 00:05:12.230 align:middle line:84%
you turn on a different
set of neural networks

00:05:12.230 --> 00:05:13.860 align:middle line:84%
in a different
combination and sequence

00:05:13.860 --> 00:05:16.060 align:middle line:84%
that produces a different
level of mind that

00:05:16.060 --> 00:05:18.380 align:middle line:84%
turns on a different
blend of chemicals for you

00:05:18.380 --> 00:05:20.560 align:middle line:84%
to feel exactly the way
you were just thinking,

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:21.600 align:middle line:90%
negative or unhappy.

00:05:21.600 --> 00:05:24.777 align:middle line:84%
Now the moment you begin
to feel the way you think,

00:05:24.777 --> 00:05:27.360 align:middle line:84%
because the brain is in constant
communication with your body,

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:29.410 align:middle line:84%
you begin to think
the way you feel.

00:05:29.410 --> 00:05:31.680 align:middle line:84%
So you begin to feel the
way you think and think

00:05:31.680 --> 00:05:33.770 align:middle line:84%
the way you feel and
feel the way you think.

00:05:33.770 --> 00:05:37.290 align:middle line:84%
And the cycle of thinking and
feeling over time conditions

00:05:37.290 --> 00:05:39.500 align:middle line:84%
the body to memorize
that emotion

00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:40.792 align:middle line:90%
better than the conscious mind.

00:05:40.792 --> 00:05:42.666 align:middle line:84%
Whenever the body knows
better than the mind,

00:05:42.666 --> 00:05:43.650 align:middle line:90%
that's called a habit.

00:05:43.650 --> 00:05:45.440 align:middle line:84%
Habit is when the
body is the mind.

00:05:45.440 --> 00:05:45.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:05:45.940 --> 00:05:47.280 align:middle line:84%
So it's not the
chicken or the egg.

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:48.780 align:middle line:84%
It's not the body
the controls the mind

00:05:48.780 --> 00:05:49.790 align:middle line:84%
or the mind that
controls the body.

00:05:49.790 --> 00:05:51.373 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: No, it's
a state of being.

00:05:51.373 --> 00:05:53.720 align:middle line:84%
Because when mind and
body are working together,

00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:55.530 align:middle line:90%
that's called a state of being.

00:05:55.530 --> 00:05:57.910 align:middle line:84%
Now, thoughts are the
language of the brain

00:05:57.910 --> 00:06:00.200 align:middle line:84%
and feelings are the
language of the body.

00:06:00.200 --> 00:06:03.590 align:middle line:84%
So when you begin to think
and feel in a certain cycle,

00:06:03.590 --> 00:06:05.650 align:middle line:90%
you create a state of being.

00:06:05.650 --> 00:06:10.270 align:middle line:84%
Now as I said, 95% of who we are
by the time we're 35 years old

00:06:10.270 --> 00:06:13.749 align:middle line:84%
is a set of memorized behaviors
in which it's subconsciously

00:06:13.749 --> 00:06:15.540 align:middle line:84%
running behind the
scenes of our awareness.

00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:16.940 align:middle line:90%
Here's a great example.

00:06:16.940 --> 00:06:19.110 align:middle line:84%
You can't consciously
remember a phone number.

00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:21.294 align:middle line:84%
Well, you'd have to
be over 35 for this.

00:06:21.294 --> 00:06:23.210 align:middle line:84%
You can't consciously
remember a phone number,

00:06:23.210 --> 00:06:25.380 align:middle line:84%
but you walk over to the
receiver and you pick it up

00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:29.080 align:middle line:84%
and you look at the dial pad and
your fingers dial the number.

00:06:29.080 --> 00:06:31.230 align:middle line:84%
You can't remember
your ATM number,

00:06:31.230 --> 00:06:32.730 align:middle line:84%
but your fingers
can remember it.

00:06:32.730 --> 00:06:35.250 align:middle line:84%
So you've practiced
it so many times

00:06:35.250 --> 00:06:37.430 align:middle line:84%
that your body knows
better than your brain.

00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:41.990 align:middle line:84%
Now 95% of who we are by
the time we're 35 years old

00:06:41.990 --> 00:06:44.270 align:middle line:84%
are those set of
memorized subconscious

00:06:44.270 --> 00:06:45.092 align:middle line:90%
automatic programs.

00:06:45.092 --> 00:06:46.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, that's
why you said 35.

00:06:46.550 --> 00:06:47.300 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Right.

00:06:47.300 --> 00:06:49.510 align:middle line:84%
So by 35 we've pretty
much figured it all out

00:06:49.510 --> 00:06:51.300 align:middle line:84%
neurologically,
become hardwired.

00:06:51.300 --> 00:06:54.270 align:middle line:84%
So now the person wants
to think positively,

00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:56.170 align:middle line:84%
but they've been
feeling negatively

00:06:56.170 --> 00:06:59.210 align:middle line:90%
for the last 25 years.

00:06:59.210 --> 00:07:01.700 align:middle line:84%
They want to create
a new life and create

00:07:01.700 --> 00:07:04.300 align:middle line:84%
a new vision for themselves,
but they feel guilty.

00:07:04.300 --> 00:07:07.050 align:middle line:10%
That's mind and body
working in opposition.

00:07:07.050 --> 00:07:09.230 align:middle line:84%
We have to recondition
the body to a new mind.

00:07:09.230 --> 00:07:10.980 align:middle line:84%
And when the body
becomes the mind then,

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:14.220 align:middle line:84%
when I said to change is to
think greater than the body.

00:07:14.220 --> 00:07:16.650 align:middle line:84%
What I mean by that is
we have to think greater

00:07:16.650 --> 00:07:20.000 align:middle line:84%
than the memorized emotions
that the body has recognized

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:21.080 align:middle line:90%
or become familiar with.

00:07:21.080 --> 00:07:21.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:07:21.810 --> 00:07:24.710 align:middle line:84%
So then these days people
are under an enormous amount

00:07:24.710 --> 00:07:28.160 align:middle line:84%
of stress, not only because of
the current economic situation

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:30.560 align:middle line:84%
but it's because of the
information and the technology

00:07:30.560 --> 00:07:34.200 align:middle line:84%
age speeding things up faster
and faster, constantly feeling

00:07:34.200 --> 00:07:36.430 align:middle line:90%
or distracted.

00:07:36.430 --> 00:07:40.440 align:middle line:84%
So what does stress do
to the mind and the body?

00:07:40.440 --> 00:07:41.290 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Mm.

00:07:41.290 --> 00:07:43.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know, stress
is when the body's

00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:44.170 align:middle line:90%
knocked out of balance.

00:07:44.170 --> 00:07:48.880 align:middle line:84%
And when you're being chased by
a lion thousands of years ago,

00:07:48.880 --> 00:07:51.160 align:middle line:84%
you turned on a
primitive nervous system

00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:54.750 align:middle line:84%
to mobilize all of this energy
to prepare you for some threat

00:07:54.750 --> 00:07:57.150 align:middle line:84%
or event in your
external environment.

00:07:57.150 --> 00:08:00.200 align:middle line:84%
And when you mobilize all that
energy, you're really saying,

00:08:00.200 --> 00:08:02.140 align:middle line:84%
I've got to take
care of this body.

00:08:02.140 --> 00:08:04.170 align:middle line:84%
I've got to become
aware of my environment

00:08:04.170 --> 00:08:06.740 align:middle line:84%
and how much time do
I have to get there.

00:08:06.740 --> 00:08:09.580 align:middle line:84%
So what was once
highly adaptive,

00:08:09.580 --> 00:08:11.547 align:middle line:84%
which means if you're
being chased by a lion,

00:08:11.547 --> 00:08:13.630 align:middle line:84%
you'd better make sure
that you have enough energy

00:08:13.630 --> 00:08:15.800 align:middle line:90%
to either fight or run.

00:08:15.800 --> 00:08:20.560 align:middle line:84%
But now if you're thinking
about firing an employee,

00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:24.040 align:middle line:84%
and you know that this
person has a wife that's sick

00:08:24.040 --> 00:08:27.930 align:middle line:84%
and they have four children,
and you know that they actually

00:08:27.930 --> 00:08:30.430 align:middle line:84%
need the job more than the other
