emotional reaction.

00:16:08.700 --> 00:16:12.680 align:middle line:84%
Now if you keep that same
refractory period going

00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:15.790 align:middle line:84%
for weeks or months, that's
called a temperament.

00:16:15.790 --> 00:16:18.265 align:middle line:90%
So you say, why is he so angry?

00:16:18.265 --> 00:16:19.840 align:middle line:84%
And you say, why
are you so angry?

00:16:19.840 --> 00:16:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And they say, well, this thing
happened to me 11 months ago.

00:16:23.190 --> 00:16:25.860 align:middle line:84%
Same refractory period
that's going on and on.

00:16:25.860 --> 00:16:29.140 align:middle line:84%
Now if you keep it
going for years on end,

00:16:29.140 --> 00:16:30.860 align:middle line:84%
that's called a
personality trait.

00:16:30.860 --> 00:16:33.630 align:middle line:84%
So by very definition,
our personality

00:16:33.630 --> 00:16:36.010 align:middle line:84%
is completely
connected to our past.

00:16:36.010 --> 00:16:39.120 align:middle line:84%
And if we live by the same
emotions every single day,

00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:41.500 align:middle line:84%
