to their body that
they've memorized.

00:17:23.869 --> 00:17:25.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So but then
it's more than just

00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:26.569 align:middle line:90%
changing it in your mind.

00:17:26.569 --> 00:17:31.350 align:middle line:84%
You're combating a physical,
chemical, body, cellular memory

00:17:31.350 --> 00:17:31.850 align:middle line:90%
reaction.

00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:32.683 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Exactly.

00:17:32.683 --> 00:17:35.650 align:middle line:84%
And the moment you interrupt
that chemical continuity,

00:17:35.650 --> 00:17:37.470 align:middle line:84%
the body, which has
become the mind,

00:17:37.470 --> 00:17:39.750 align:middle line:84%
begins to send signals
back to the brain.

00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:42.330 align:middle line:84%
So you started out with
really good intentions,

00:17:42.330 --> 00:17:44.010 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden
two hours go by

00:17:44.010 --> 00:17:47.640 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden the cells
of the body get together

00:17:47.640 --> 00:17:48.425 align:middle line:90%
and say, hey.

00:17:48.425 --> 00:17:50.460 align:middle line:84%
We've modified
our receptor sites

00:17:50.460 --> 00:17:52.194 align:middle line:84%
to receive more
chemicals of guilt.

00:17:52.194 --> 00:17:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And all of the
sudden you're going

00:17:53.610 --> 00:17:55.680 align:middle line:90%
to stop after 20 years of this?

00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:58.510 align:middle line:84%
So the body sends a signal back
up the central nervous system.

00:17:58.510 --> 00:18:00.190 align:middle line:90%
I call that the fast track.

00:18:00.190 --> 00:18:02.340 align:middle line:84%
At the same time,
chemical levels,

00:18:02.340 --> 00:18:05.090 align:middle line:84%
those peptides that we
produce that are feelings,

00:18:05.090 --> 00:18:07.560 align:middle line:84%
begin to drop because you're
no longer feeling suffering.

00:18:07.560 --> 00:18:11.120 align:middle line:84%
And all of the sudden the
thermostat in the brain

00:18:11.120 --> 00:18:13.560 align:middle line:84%
called the hypothalamus
notices that circulating

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:15.230 align:middle line:84%
levels of suffering
is going down.

00:18:15.230 --> 00:18:18.010 align:middle line:84%
So it sends a signal back
to the thinking brain

00:18:18.010 --> 00:18:19.240 align:middle line:90%
that's called the slow track.

00:18:19.240 --> 00:18:20.823 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing
you know, you start

00:18:20.823 --> 00:18:23.722 align:middle line:84%
to hear these sub
vocalizations in your head.

00:18:23.722 --> 00:18:24.680 align:middle line:90%
That chatter, you know?

00:18:24.680 --> 00:18:26.850 align:middle line:84%
That awfulizing that
starts saying, like,

00:18:26.850 --> 00:18:28.549 align:middle line:90%
maybe you should start tomorrow.

00:18:28.549 --> 00:18:29.840 align:middle line:90%
Tomorrow would be a better day.

00:18:29.840 --> 00:18:32.700 align:middle line:90%
Or ooh, this doesn't feel right.

00:18:32.700 --> 00:18:33.210 align:middle line:90%
Ew.

00:18:33.210 --> 00:18:34.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it starts
to defend itself.

00:18:34.630 --> 00:18:36.213 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
the body as the mind

00:18:36.213 --> 00:18:38.295 align:middle line:84%
says, where've you been
for the last 20 years?

00:18:38.295 --> 00:18:39.420 align:middle line:90%
I've been running the show.

00:18:39.420 --> 00:18:40.810 align:middle line:84%
You think you've been
running the show,

00:18:40.810 --> 00:18:42.320 align:middle line:90%
and now you're going to change?

00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:43.260 align:middle line:90%
We can't have this.

00:18:43.260 --> 00:18:45.510 align:middle line:84%
And so the body, when I say
the change must be greater

00:18:45.510 --> 00:18:47.890 align:middle line:84%
than the body, I
literally mean that you

00:18:47.890 --> 00:18:51.670 align:middle line:84%
have to overcome the chatter
and the voices in your head.

00:18:51.670 --> 00:18:56.290 align:middle line:84%
Because the moment you respond
to that voice as if it's true,

00:18:56.290 --> 00:18:59.350 align:middle line:84%
consciousness immerses
itself back into the program.

00:18:59.350 --> 00:19:01.590 align:middle line:84%
And we return back to
the same personality,

00:19:01.590 --> 00:19:04.660 align:middle line:84%
thinking the same thoughts,
performing the same actions,

00:19:04.660 --> 00:19:06.830 align:middle line:84%
living by the same emotions,
and really expecting

00:19:06.830 --> 00:19:08.580 align:middle line:84%
something different
to happen in our life.

00:19:08.580 --> 00:19:09.996 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Eating the
same bad foods,

00:19:09.996 --> 00:19:12.470 align:middle line:84%
going back to the smoking
habit, addiction, addiction.

00:19:12.470 --> 00:19:14.190 align:middle line:84%
So is this the same
thing for, say,

00:19:14.190 --> 00:19:17.186 align:middle line:84%
an addiction to
alcohol or to drugs?

00:19:17.186 --> 00:19:18.810 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
think about this, OK?

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:20.710 align:middle line:84%
Let's say that a
person has an event

00:19:20.710 --> 00:19:24.010 align:middle line:90%
in their life many years prior.

00:19:24.010 --> 00:19:27.150 align:middle line:84%
And they're branded emotionally
from that experience.

00:19:27.150 --> 00:19:29.980 align:middle line:84%
And they can't get
beyond the experience

00:19:29.980 --> 00:19:31.860 align:middle line:84%
any longer because
they're emotionally

00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:33.450 align:middle line:90%
living by that same state.

00:19:33.450 --> 00:19:37.120 align:middle line:84%
In other words, they got knocked
out of balance some time ago.

00:19:37.120 --> 00:19:41.330 align:middle line:84%
And so now the person now all
of the sudden is going to say,

00:19:41.330 --> 00:19:43.740 align:middle line:84%
I've got to make
this feeling go away.

00:19:43.740 --> 00:19:47.640 align:middle line:84%
And so I don't know how
to change it inside of me,

00:19:47.640 --> 00:19:50.260 align:middle line:84%
so I'm going to look for
something outside of me that's

00:19:50.260 --> 00:19:51.360 align:middle line:90%
going to make it go away.

00:19:51.360 --> 00:19:52.151 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To numb it.

00:19:52.151 --> 00:19:54.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Now, drugs
or alcohol or shopping

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:57.680 align:middle line:84%
or gambling or pornography
or video gaming or overeating

00:19:57.680 --> 00:20:01.510 align:middle line:84%
or undereating, all
of that stuff produces

00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:04.460 align:middle line:84%
an immediate internal
chemical change.

00:20:04.460 --> 00:20:07.580 align:middle line:84%
And the moment you notice
that that pain goes away,

00:20:07.580 --> 00:20:11.010 align:middle line:84%
you pay attention to whatever
or whoever caused that.

00:20:11.010 --> 00:20:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And that event, in and of
itself, that association

00:20:13.960 --> 00:20:15.020 align:middle line:90%
is called a memory.

00:20:15.020 --> 00:20:19.040 align:middle line:84%
And so we begin to
associate, unconsciously,

00:20:19.040 --> 00:20:22.110 align:middle line:84%
things in our outside
environment that make that pain

00:20:22.110 --> 00:20:22.620 align:middle line:90%
go away.

00:20:22.620 --> 00:20:24.130 align:middle line:90%
Now here's the problem.

00:20:24.130 --> 00:20:26.520 align:middle line:84%
Every time the person
gambles or shops

00:20:26.520 --> 00:20:30.130 align:middle line:84%
or video games, their pleasure
centers in their brain

00:20:30.130 --> 00:20:33.160 align:middle line:84%
start going higher and higher,
recalibrating to a higher level

00:20:33.160 --> 00:20:36.300 align:middle line:84%
because the receptor sites
on the outside of the cells

00:20:36.300 --> 00:20:37.880 align:middle line:90%
become desensitized.

00:20:37.880 --> 00:20:40.870 align:middle line:84%
So the next time you
gamble, the next time you

00:20:40.870 --> 00:20:42.720 align:middle line:84%
shop, the next time
you use a drug, you

00:20:42.720 --> 00:20:45.110 align:middle line:84%
need a little bit more to
turn on those receptor sites.

00:20:45.110 --> 00:20:47.459 align:middle line:84%
It's like living with a spouse
that always yells at you.

00:20:47.459 --> 00:20:49.000 align:middle line:84%
They have to yell
a little bit louder

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:51.960 align:middle line:84%
to get your attention because
you've become desensitized.

00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:54.090 align:middle line:84%
So now the pleasure
centers become

00:20:54.090 --> 00:20:56.330 align:middle line:84%
re-calibrated to
such a high level

00:20:56.330 --> 00:20:58.862 align:middle line:84%
that in the absence
of that stimulation,

00:20:58.862 --> 00:21:01.320 align:middle line:84%
people don't feel any pleasure
from anything in their life.

00:21:01.320 --> 00:21:04.190 align:middle line:84%
So then they're looking
for some immediate way

00:21:04.190 --> 00:21:07.260 align:middle line:84%
to take that pain away because
they don't know that it really

00:21:07.260 --> 00:21:08.900 align:middle line:90%
has to happen from within them.

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:11.700 align:middle line:84%
So behind every
substance addiction,

00:21:11.700 --> 00:21:14.120 align:middle line:84%
there's usually an
emotion that we've

00:21:14.120 --> 00:21:16.420 align:middle line:84%
memorized that's become
part of our identity

00:21:16.420 --> 00:21:18.220 align:middle line:84%
that we don't know
how to change.

00:21:18.220 --> 00:21:21.000 align:middle line:84%
So the survival emotions,
when you're knocked out

00:21:21.000 --> 00:21:23.170 align:middle line:84%
of homeostasis,
knocked out of balance,

00:21:23.170 --> 00:21:26.330 align:middle line:84%
the emotions of anger
and aggression and hatred

00:21:26.330 --> 00:21:30.010 align:middle line:84%
and judgment and fear and
anxiety and insecurity

00:21:30.010 --> 00:21:32.810 align:middle line:84%
and hopelessness and
powerlessness, depression,

00:21:32.810 --> 00:21:36.675 align:middle line:84%
those altered states of
consciousness I call them,

00:21:36.675 --> 00:21:38.800 align:middle line:84%
are pretty much the normal
states of consciousness.

00:21:38.800 --> 00:21:41.220 align:middle line:84%
But they're all driven by
the hormones of stress.

00:21:41.220 --> 00:21:41.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Amazing.

00:21:41.940 --> 00:21:43.616 align:middle line:84%
So to follow this,
there was again,

00:21:43.616 --> 00:21:44.990 align:middle line:84%
in the movie you
