You're going to have to
do something differently.

00:26:06.440 --> 00:26:07.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Physiologically.

00:26:07.430 --> 00:26:09.100 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: If you
change your behavior,

00:26:09.100 --> 00:26:12.760 align:middle line:84%
get your behaviors to match
your intentions or your actions

00:26:12.760 --> 00:26:14.140 align:middle line:90%
equal to your thoughts.

00:26:14.140 --> 00:26:16.580 align:middle line:84%
If you get mind and
body working together,

00:26:16.580 --> 00:26:18.790 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
a new experience.

00:26:18.790 --> 00:26:20.940 align:middle line:84%
Now the moment you
have a new experience,

00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:23.600 align:middle line:84%
you activate the second
brain called the limbic brain

00:26:23.600 --> 00:26:25.600 align:middle line:84%
or the chemical brain
or the emotional bring.

00:26:25.600 --> 00:26:27.040 align:middle line:90%
Now let me explain.

00:26:27.040 --> 00:26:29.100 align:middle line:84%
When you're in the
midst of an experience,

00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:31.570 align:middle line:84%
everything you're seeing
and smelling and tasting

00:26:31.570 --> 00:26:34.060 align:middle line:84%
and feeling and hearing,
all of your five senses

00:26:34.060 --> 00:26:36.220 align:middle line:90%
plug you into the environment.

00:26:36.220 --> 00:26:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And as you're gathering
all this sensory data

00:26:38.410 --> 00:26:41.080 align:middle line:84%
from your external world,
all that information's

00:26:41.080 --> 00:26:44.730 align:middle line:84%
rushing back to your brain
through five sensory pathways.

00:26:44.730 --> 00:26:47.200 align:middle line:84%
The moment all that
information reaches your brain,

00:26:47.200 --> 00:26:50.070 align:middle line:84%
jungles of neurons begin
to organize themselves

00:26:50.070 --> 00:26:52.640 align:middle line:84%
into pattern to
reflect the event.

00:26:52.640 --> 00:26:56.080 align:middle line:84%
The moment they string into
place, the limbic brain

00:26:56.080 --> 00:26:57.925 align:middle line:84%
or the emotional brain
releases a chemical.

00:26:57.925 --> 00:27:00.580 align:middle line:84%
And that chemical's
called a feeling.

00:27:00.580 --> 00:27:02.940 align:middle line:84%
So feelings and emotions
are the end product

00:27:02.940 --> 00:27:04.460 align:middle line:90%
of past experiences.

00:27:04.460 --> 00:27:06.100 align:middle line:84%
And we can remember
experiences better

00:27:06.100 --> 00:27:08.220 align:middle line:84%
because we can
remember how they felt.

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:10.340 align:middle line:84%
So you can remember
where you were on 9/11.

00:27:10.340 --> 00:27:12.920 align:middle line:84%
You can tell me who you
were with, the time of day

00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:14.200 align:middle line:90%
it was, what you were doing.

00:27:14.200 --> 00:27:16.210 align:middle line:84%
You can tell me everything
about that moment.

00:27:16.210 --> 00:27:19.820 align:middle line:84%
Because everything you were
seeing and hearing and feeling,

00:27:19.820 --> 00:27:21.420 align:middle line:84%
it changed your
internal chemistry

00:27:21.420 --> 00:27:23.610 align:middle line:84%
and caused your
brain to wake up,

00:27:23.610 --> 00:27:25.680 align:middle line:84%
and you paid attention
to what caused it.

00:27:25.680 --> 00:27:30.330 align:middle line:84%
So if you read the book on
compassion as an example,

00:27:30.330 --> 00:27:33.790 align:middle line:84%
and you read it three times, and
you have all this information

00:27:33.790 --> 00:27:36.070 align:middle line:84%
wired in your
thinking neocortex,

00:27:36.070 --> 00:27:39.330 align:middle line:84%
and you could run around your
life and say to your friends,

00:27:39.330 --> 00:27:41.180 align:middle line:84%
you know, you need to
be more compassionate

00:27:41.180 --> 00:27:43.560 align:middle line:90%
and you need to forgive more.

00:27:43.560 --> 00:27:46.830 align:middle line:84%
What you're doing is you're
basically espousing philosophy.

00:27:46.830 --> 00:27:50.931 align:middle line:84%
But then if you get a call
from your spouse and he says,

00:27:50.931 --> 00:27:51.430 align:middle line:90%
listen.

00:27:51.430 --> 00:27:53.800 align:middle line:84%
We have to go to
dinner with my mother.

00:27:53.800 --> 00:27:55.820 align:middle line:84%
And you don't like
your mother-in-law.

00:27:55.820 --> 00:27:58.430 align:middle line:84%
Well, here's now where
the rubber meets the road.

00:27:58.430 --> 00:28:01.470 align:middle line:84%
Because if you pull over
on the side of the road

00:28:01.470 --> 00:28:06.240 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden you notice
those unconscious thoughts,

00:28:06.240 --> 00:28:10.940 align:middle line:84%
and you begin to pay attention
to those impulsive behaviors,

00:28:10.940 --> 00:28:14.240 align:middle line:84%
and you start to notice the
feelings that you're feeling.

00:28:14.240 --> 00:28:18.670 align:middle line:84%
And as you pull over on the side
of the road and you say, OK.

00:28:18.670 --> 00:28:22.310 align:middle line:84%
Let me restrain these thoughts,
behaviors, and emotions.

00:28:22.310 --> 00:28:26.680 align:middle line:84%
As you begin to observe those
states of mind and body,

00:28:26.680 --> 00:28:29.110 align:middle line:84%
you're actually turning
on the frontal lobe.

00:28:29.110 --> 00:28:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And the frontal
lobe is beginning

00:28:30.760 --> 00:28:33.520 align:middle line:84%
to quiet down the
circuits in your brain

00:28:33.520 --> 00:28:35.260 align:middle line:84%
that are connected
to the old self.

00:28:35.260 --> 00:28:37.970 align:middle line:84%
And if nerve cells that
no longer fire together

00:28:37.970 --> 00:28:41.540 align:middle line:84%
no longer wire together, you're
turning off that level of mind.

00:28:41.540 --> 00:28:43.670 align:middle line:90%
Now if you said, let me see.

00:28:43.670 --> 00:28:45.090 align:middle line:90%
What did the book say?

00:28:45.090 --> 00:28:47.240 align:middle line:84%
Oh, it said to
see myself in her.

00:28:47.240 --> 00:28:48.000 align:middle line:90%
Oh, OK.

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:49.470 align:middle line:90%
I'll try that out.

00:28:49.470 --> 00:28:52.650 align:middle line:84%
Oh, it said to stay present
and not hold her to the past.

00:28:52.650 --> 00:28:54.830 align:middle line:84%
And as you begin to
sit there and think

00:28:54.830 --> 00:28:57.840 align:middle line:84%
about a new way of
being, you would

00:28:57.840 --> 00:29:00.160 align:middle line:84%
begin to cause
your brain to fire

00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:02.030 align:middle line:90%
in new sequences, new patterns.

00:29:02.030 --> 00:29:04.280 align:middle line:84%
And whenever you make the
brain work differently,

00:29:04.280 --> 00:29:05.540 align:middle line:90%
you're changing your mind.

00:29:05.540 --> 00:29:07.020 align:middle line:90%
Mind is the brain in action.

00:29:07.020 --> 00:29:10.400 align:middle line:84%
So as you begin to rehearse
mentally a new way of being,

00:29:10.400 --> 00:29:12.780 align:middle line:84%
and at the same time
you take that knowledge

00:29:12.780 --> 00:29:15.240 align:middle line:84%
and you put yourself
into the equation,

00:29:15.240 --> 00:29:18.810 align:middle line:84%
as you begin to think
about a new way of being,

00:29:18.810 --> 00:29:21.440 align:middle line:84%
not only are you making
the brain work in new ways,

00:29:21.440 --> 00:29:23.700 align:middle line:84%
but nerve cells that fire
together, wire together.

00:29:23.700 --> 00:29:27.550 align:middle line:84%
You're beginning to install
the neurological hardware

00:29:27.550 --> 00:29:31.302 align:middle line:84%
in your brain to have some
circuits in place to use when

00:29:31.302 --> 00:29:33.010 align:middle line:84%
you go to dinner with
your mother-in-law.

00:29:33.010 --> 00:29:35.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So does it have
to be an event that

00:29:35.530 --> 00:29:37.785 align:middle line:84%
requires the sensing
and the thinking

00:29:37.785 --> 00:29:40.710 align:middle line:90%
and the feeling and the hearing?

00:29:40.710 --> 00:29:43.602 align:middle line:84%
Like, there's a reason why
you remember a bad birthday as

00:29:43.602 --> 00:29:45.060 align:middle line:84%
opposed to a really
great birthday,

00:29:45.060 --> 00:29:48.610 align:middle line:84%
because it fires in the
body chemically different.

00:29:48.610 --> 00:29:49.110 align:middle line:90%
Correct?

00:29:49.110 --> 00:29:49.750 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you're saying?

00:29:49.750 --> 00:29:51.910 align:middle line:84%
So rather than just reading
the book on compassion,

00:29:51.910 --> 00:29:54.731 align:middle line:84%
you actually have to practice
it in a heightened state

00:29:54.731 --> 00:29:56.606 align:middle line:84%
so that you're using
all five senses in order

00:29:56.606 --> 00:29:57.110 align:middle line:90%
for it to change?

00:29:57.110 --> 00:29:59.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: You don't actually
have to use your five senses,

00:29:59.070 --> 00:30:00.170 align:middle line:90%
but here's the caveat.

00:30:00.170 --> 00:30:02.910 align:middle line:10%
Let's just say now you
walk into the dinner

00:30:02.910 --> 00:30:05.720 align:middle line:10%
with your mother-in-law and
you've cultivated a new mind

00:30:05.720 --> 00:30:08.730 align:middle line:10%
because you sat on the side
of the road for 45 minutes

00:30:08.730 --> 00:30:11.120 align:middle line:10%
and got your mind and
body working together.

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:14.940 align:middle line:84%
You began to fire and wire
new circuits in your brain.

00:30:14.940 --> 00:30:17.480 align:middle line:84%
And you stopped the chemicals
from running to your body

00:30:17.480 --> 00:30:19.911 align:middle line:84%
and you began to think
about a new way of being,

00:30:19.911 --> 00:30:21.660 align:middle line:84%
and you started to
think about compassion.

00:30:21.660 --> 00:30:24.254 align:middle line:84%
And you walk in there and
you get your behaviors

00:30:24.254 --> 00:30:26.170 align:middle line:84%
to match your intentions,
you get your actions

00:30:26.170 --> 00:30:26.990 align:middle line:90%
equal to your thoughts.

00:30:26.990 --> 00:30:28.900 align:middle line:84%
You get your mind and
body working together,

00:30:28.900 --> 00:30:30.750 align:middle line:84%
and you do exactly
what the book says,

00:30:30.750 --> 00:30:33.083 align:middle line:84%
and you're sitting in the
presence of your mother-in-law

00:30:33.083 --> 00:30:36.800 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden, you
start to feel compassion.

00:30:36.800 --> 00:30:39.630 align:middle line:84%
The moment you begin
to feel compassion,

00:30:39.630 --> 00:30:41.120 align:middle line:90%
you turn on that limbic brain.

00:30:41.120 --> 00:30:44.200 align:middle line:84%
Now you're teaching
your body chemically.

00:30:44.200 --> 00:30:46.350 align:middle line:84%
You're instructing
it chemically so

00:30:46.350 --> 00:30:49.390 align:middle line:84%
that it learns what your mind
has intellectually understood.

00:30:49.390 --> 00:30:52.830 align:middle line:84%
Now, knowledge is for the mind,
but experience is for the body.

00:30:52.830 --> 00:30:55.440 align:middle line:84%
And the moment you
feel compassion, now

00:30:55.440 --> 00:30:56.850 align:middle line:90%
you're embodying knowledge.

00:30:56.850 --> 00:30:58.500 align:middle line:90%
The word is becoming flesh.

00:30:58.500 --> 00:31:01.020 align:middle line:84%
You begin to signal
new genes and new ways,

00:31:01.020 --> 00:31:04.230 align:middle line:84%
and you begin to change
your very state of being.

00:31:04.230 --> 00:31:06.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We have a whole clip
that shows this in an animated

00:31:06.810 --> 00:31:10.330 align:middle line:84%
way so that people can,
again, follow along at home.

00:31:10.330 --> 00:31:12.590 align:middle line:90%
So I want to explain.

00:31:12.590 --> 00:31:14.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
this is a good clip

00:31:14.210 --> 00:31:16.280 align:middle line:84%
of just showing
the three brains.

00:31:16.280 --> 00:31:18.400 align:middle line:84%
That yellow brain that
sits on the outside

00:31:18.400 --> 00:31:20.950 align:middle line:84%
is your thinking
bring, your neocortex.

00:31:20.950 --> 00:31:23.220 align:middle line:84%
Right underneath that,
about the size of a lemon,

00:31:23.220 --> 00:31:26.390 align:middle line:84%
is your emotional brain or
chemical brain or limbic brain

00:31:26.390 --> 00:31:27.050 align:middle line:90%
or mid brain.

00:31:27.050 --> 00:31:30.030 align:middle line:84%
And that red brain in the back
is called your being brain,

00:31:30.030 --> 00:31:32.270 align:middle line:84%
which we'll talk
about right now.

00:31:32.270 --> 00:31:34.260 align:middle line:84%
When you're in a
state of being, it

00:31:34.260 --> 00:31:38.130 align:middle line:84%
means that your mind and
body are working as one.

00:31:38.130 --> 00:31:40.750 align:middle line:84%
So you can't forgive your
mother-in-law or show

00:31:40.750 --> 00:31:44.440 align:middle line:84%
compassion one time and expect
to be put on the stained glass

00:31:44.440 --> 00:31:46.050 align:middle line:90%
windows in church.

00:31:46.050 --> 00:31:48.480 align:middle line:84%
You have to be able to replicate
it over and over again.

00:31:48.480 --> 00:31:50.146 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Ah, for it
to make a difference.

00:31:50.146 --> 00:31:52.890 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And when you can
do it over and over again,

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:56.900 align:middle line:84%
you will begin to
neurochemically condition

00:31:56.900 --> 00:32:00.942 align:middle line:84%
your body to memorize compassion
as well as your conscious mind.

00:32:00.942 --> 00:32:02.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now there's
some clips that

00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:03.983 align:middle line:84%
are coming up that
I want to show here

00:32:03.983 --> 00:32:07.370 align:middle line:84%
that really show how
this works in the brain.

00:32:07.370 --> 00:32:09.830 align:middle line:84%
These are the ones that
made a massive impact on me.

00:32:09.830 --> 00:32:11.960 align:middle line:84%
You say that they do for
most people who see it.

00:32:11.960 --> 00:32:14.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: But let me
just get this last point

00:32:14.070 --> 00:32:14.991 align:middle line:90%
before we show it.

00:32:14.991 --> 00:32:15.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:32:15.490 --> 00:32:18.260 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So then when you
do it enough times, you repeat

00:32:18.260 --> 00:32:21.160 align:middle line:84%
the experience enough
times, your mind and body

00:32:21.160 --> 00:32:22.370 align:middle line:90%
begin to work together.

00:32:22.370 --> 00:32:24.980 align:middle line:84%
You activate that third
brain called the cerebellum.

00:32:24.980 --> 00:32:27.110 align:middle line:84%
That's the seat of
your subconscious.

00:32:27.110 --> 00:32:28.900 align:middle line:84%
When you are in
a state of being,

00:32:28.900 --> 00:32:30.920 align:middle line:84%
your mind and body
are working together.

00:32:30.920 --> 00:32:34.970 align:middle line:84%
And we could say that you've
memorized an internal chemical

00:32:34.970 --> 00:32:38.970 align:middle line:84%
order that no person, no thing,
no experience outside of you

00:32:38.970 --> 00:32:39.920 align:middle line:90%
can move you from it.

00:32:39.920 --> 00:32:41.870 align:middle line:84%
And when you're in
that state of being,

00:32:41.870 --> 00:32:44.700 align:middle line:84%
now we're mastering
that information.

00:32:44.700 --> 00:32:46.400 align:middle line:90%
It's becoming wisdom.

00:32:46.400 --> 00:32:49.420 align:middle line:84%
And now that state of
compassion is innate.

00:32:49.420 --> 00:32:50.340 align:middle line:90%
It's in us.

00:32:50.340 --> 00:32:52.040 align:middle line:84%
And then when we're
in that state,

00:32:52.040 --> 00:32:53.840 align:middle line:84%
then the environment
is no longer

00:32:53.840 --> 00:32:56.080 align:middle line:84%
controlling how
we think and feel.

00:32:56.080 --> 00:32:58.100 align:middle line:84%
Now how we think and
feel is beginning

00:32:58.100 --> 00:32:59.380 align:middle line:90%
to affect our environment.

00:32:59.380 --> 00:33:01.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this could
happen at any age.

00:33:01.100 --> 00:33:01.880 align:middle line:90%
You can do this at any point.

00:33:01.880 --> 00:33:02.540 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Absolutely.

00:33:02.540 --> 00:33:03.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is what change is.

00:33:03.630 --> 00:33:05.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: And we were talking
about the golf swing earlier.

00:33:05.480 --> 00:33:06.438 align:middle line:90%
That's a great example.

00:33:06.438 --> 00:33:09.180 align:middle line:84%
But let's take it to
more altruistic measures.

00:33:09.180 --> 00:33:14.410 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about compassion
or forgiveness or success

00:33:14.410 --> 00:33:15.030 align:middle line:90%
or wealth.

00:33:15.030 --> 00:33:17.011 align:middle line:84%
It works the same
exact way for anything.

00:33:17.011 --> 00:33:17.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

