>>DISPENZA: Learning first,
then you get the thinking brain.

00:33:20.570 --> 00:33:23.369 align:middle line:84%
Then you perform the action,
you get your behaviors

00:33:23.369 --> 00:33:24.410 align:middle line:90%
to match your intentions.

00:33:24.410 --> 00:33:26.930 align:middle line:84%
You embody that information,
then it becomes innate.

00:33:26.930 --> 00:33:29.015 align:middle line:84%
And when you're in that
state where it's in you,

00:33:29.015 --> 00:33:32.160 align:middle line:84%
it's who you are, then you
can say, I am successful.

00:33:32.160 --> 00:33:33.170 align:middle line:90%
I am compassionate.

00:33:33.170 --> 00:33:34.400 align:middle line:90%
I am patient.

00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:36.990 align:middle line:84%
Because your mind and
body are working together,

00:33:36.990 --> 00:33:38.972 align:middle line:84%
and it's no longer a
philosophical concept.

00:33:38.972 --> 00:33:39.930 align:middle line:90%
You know that you know.

00:33:39.930 --> 00:33:42.263 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, let's see what
it looks like in the brain.

00:33:42.263 --> 00:33:44.280 align:middle line:84%
What does it physically
look like in the brain?

00:33:44.280 --> 00:33:44.620 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Sure.

00:33:44.620 --> 00:33:45.290 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:33:45.290 --> 00:33:46.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, so
this is a clip of--

00:33:46.800 --> 00:33:47.970 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So
this is two neurons

00:33:47.970 --> 00:33:49.980 align:middle line:84%
that have developed a
long term relationship.

00:33:49.980 --> 00:33:51.920 align:middle line:84%
They've fired and
wired together,

00:33:51.920 --> 00:33:56.200 align:middle line:84%
and now they're hardwired
into a very specific pattern.

00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:58.320 align:middle line:84%
You can show the
next one, too, here.

00:33:58.320 --> 00:34:01.990 align:middle line:84%
Again, the moment they're
in a long term relationship,

00:34:01.990 --> 00:34:04.330 align:middle line:84%
they've become a
hardwired set of circuits

00:34:04.330 --> 00:34:07.240 align:middle line:84%
that could be related to
joy or pain or unhappiness,

00:34:07.240 --> 00:34:09.250 align:middle line:84%
but it looks exactly
the same in the brain.

00:34:09.250 --> 00:34:13.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So tell me what these
are that we're looking at.

00:34:13.250 --> 00:34:14.250 align:middle line:90%
>>DISPENZA: Two neurons.

00:34:14.250 --> 00:34:19.320 align:middle line:84%
Two neurons that have
been connected or synapsed

00:34:19.320 --> 00:34:21.850 align:middle line:84%
so that now they're
exchanging information.

00:34:21.850 --> 00:34:26.130 align:middle line:84%
And neurons, they possess
the unique ability

00:34:26.130 --> 00:34:28.980 align:middle line:84%
to store and communicate
information between each other,

00:34:28.980 --> 00:34:30.730 align:middle line:90%
and they're electrochemical.

00:34:30.730 --> 00:34:34.530 align:middle line:84%
And so when you fire
a thought, information

00:34:34.530 --> 00:34:37.699 align:middle line:84%
is traveling electrochemically
from one neuron to the next.

00:34:37.699 --> 00:34:40.010 align:middle line:84%
And when it passes from
one neuron to the next,

00:34:40.010 --> 00:34:43.022 align:middle line:84%
it's exchanging information, and
that creates a state of mind.

