00:43:22.150 --> 00:43:23.150 align:middle line:90%
emotionally.

00:43:23.150 --> 00:43:27.120 align:middle line:84%
So they'll turn into
the 14-year-old child

00:43:27.120 --> 00:43:30.400 align:middle line:84%
again, because that's when
they stopped evolving.

00:43:30.400 --> 00:43:32.730 align:middle line:84%
So if feelings and emotions
are the end product

00:43:32.730 --> 00:43:35.290 align:middle line:84%
of past experiences and
you haven't overcome

00:43:35.290 --> 00:43:37.800 align:middle line:84%
an emotion in your
life, then you're

00:43:37.800 --> 00:43:39.480 align:middle line:90%
literally living in the past.

00:43:39.480 --> 00:43:42.480 align:middle line:84%
And the moment your environment
begins to signal neurologically

00:43:42.480 --> 00:43:44.670 align:middle line:84%
and chemically who
you are, you literally

00:43:44.670 --> 00:43:47.445 align:middle line:90%
go back to that program again.

00:43:47.445 --> 00:43:48.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Can you override it?

00:43:48.730 --> 00:43:51.170 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: We have to get
beyond the analytical mind,

00:43:51.170 --> 00:43:54.460 align:middle line:84%
get beyond the conscious mind,
and enter into the subconscious

00:43:54.460 --> 00:43:56.880 align:middle line:84%
mind where we can begin to
make measurable changes.

00:43:56.880 --> 00:44:00.110 align:middle line:84%
Because talk therapy's not going
to change it because all you're

00:44:00.110 --> 00:44:03.410 align:middle line:84%
doing is reaffirming it
neurologically and emotionally

00:44:03.410 --> 00:44:05.730 align:middle line:84%
conditioning your body
to remember who you are.

00:44:05.730 --> 00:44:07.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how do you get
to that sort of process?

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:08.100 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
the process of change

00:44:08.100 --> 00:44:10.060 align:middle line:84%
requires unlearning
and relearning.

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:13.110 align:middle line:84%
It requires breaking a
habit of your old self

00:44:13.110 --> 00:44:14.860 align:middle line:90%
and reinventing a new self.

00:44:14.860 --> 00:44:17.270 align:middle line:84%
It requires pruning
synaptic connections

00:44:17.270 --> 00:44:18.900 align:middle line:90%
and sprouting new connections.

00:44:18.900 --> 00:44:22.470 align:middle line:84%
It requires unmemorizing
an emotion in your body

00:44:22.470 --> 00:44:25.585 align:middle line:84%
and then reconditioning
the body to a new mind

00:44:25.585 --> 00:44:26.680 align:middle line:90%
or to a new emotion.

00:44:26.680 --> 00:44:30.500 align:middle line:84%
It literally means moving from
your past into a new future.

00:44:30.500 --> 00:44:32.840 align:middle line:84%
And so the biological
model of change

00:44:32.840 --> 00:44:36.270 align:middle line:84%
says that it's not enough
to just think positively.

00:44:36.270 --> 00:44:38.710 align:middle line:84%
You have to get down
to those emotions.

00:44:38.710 --> 00:44:41.100 align:middle line:84%
Now people would
say, well, you don't

00:44:41.100 --> 00:44:42.822 align:middle line:84%
want the child to
relive the abuse.

00:44:42.822 --> 00:44:44.530 align:middle line:84%
And I would say, you're
absolutely right.

00:44:44.530 --> 00:44:46.680 align:middle line:90%
Forget about the event.

00:44:46.680 --> 00:44:48.290 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing to
do with the event.

00:44:48.290 --> 00:44:50.040 align:middle line:90%
Go back to the emotion.

00:44:50.040 --> 00:44:52.280 align:middle line:84%
And when you can begin
to work with that emotion

00:44:52.280 --> 00:44:55.370 align:middle line:84%
and transmute that emotion
into an elevated emotion

00:44:55.370 --> 00:44:58.920 align:middle line:84%
of forgiveness or
compassion or gratitude,

00:44:58.920 --> 00:45:03.840 align:middle line:84%
the moment you begin to free
the body from that mind,

00:45:03.840 --> 00:45:05.890 align:middle line:84%
when that begins
to happen, the body

00:45:05.890 --> 00:45:08.500 align:middle line:84%
begins to break
free from the past.

00:45:08.500 --> 00:45:12.000 align:middle line:84%
And the side effect of that
liberation is called joy.

00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:15.240 align:middle line:84%
Because the body is no longer
held to the chains of the past.

00:45:15.240 --> 00:45:18.750 align:middle line:84%
And that liberation then
begins to lower the volume

00:45:18.750 --> 00:45:19.880 align:middle line:90%
to the emotional charge.

00:45:19.880 --> 00:45:21.380 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
we begin to see it

00:45:21.380 --> 00:45:24.470 align:middle line:84%
without the filter of
that emotional experience.

00:45:24.470 --> 00:45:27.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you could practice
compassion by practicing joy,

00:45:27.700 --> 00:45:30.070 align:middle line:84%
by practicing love,
you can literally--

00:45:30.070 --> 00:45:31.600 align:middle line:90%
does the next clip show that?

00:45:31.600 --> 00:45:32.480 align:middle line:90%
The blue one?

00:45:32.480 --> 00:45:33.490 align:middle line:90%
Does it show how--

00:45:33.490 --> 00:45:34.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Well,
this next clip shows

00:45:34.710 --> 00:45:36.030 align:middle line:84%
what a new experience
looks like.

00:45:36.030 --> 00:45:36.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:45:36.390 --> 00:45:38.764 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So when you're in
the midst of an experience,

00:45:38.764 --> 00:45:40.430 align:middle line:84%
gangs of neurons or
jungles of neurons

00:45:40.430 --> 00:45:43.330 align:middle line:84%
begin to organize
themselves to reflect

00:45:43.330 --> 00:45:44.980 align:middle line:90%
the external event in your life.

00:45:44.980 --> 00:45:48.610 align:middle line:84%
And so when people are no
longer having new experiences,

00:45:48.610 --> 00:45:51.840 align:middle line:84%
they're not doing anything new
or having new events take place

00:45:51.840 --> 00:45:54.800 align:middle line:84%
in their life, their brains
stays actually the same.

00:45:54.800 --> 00:45:58.810 align:middle line:84%
So if a person has
difficulty in their life,

00:45:58.810 --> 00:46:02.330 align:middle line:84%
I don't care how big
the trauma has been.

00:46:02.330 --> 00:46:05.400 align:middle line:84%
There is a biological
basis for change,

00:46:05.400 --> 00:46:08.640 align:middle line:84%
both neurologically in the
brain and epigenetically

00:46:08.640 --> 00:46:10.130 align:middle line:90%
and chemically in the body.

00:46:10.130 --> 00:46:13.370 align:middle line:84%
And all we have to do is
just find the right way

00:46:13.370 --> 00:46:16.812 align:middle line:84%
to begin to change
those unwanted patterns

00:46:16.812 --> 00:46:18.020 align:middle line:90%
into something more positive.

00:46:18.020 --> 00:46:20.200 align:middle line:84%
And one of the elements,
of course, that I use

00:46:20.200 --> 00:46:22.489 align:middle line:84%
is meditation, but there's
several ways to do it.

00:46:22.489 --> 00:46:24.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: OK, so we're going
to take a quick break.

00:46:24.530 --> 00:46:26.613 align:middle line:84%
When we come back we're
