I'm Lisa Garr, and I'm speaking
with neuroscientist Dr. Joe

00:46:38.650 --> 00:46:41.780 align:middle line:10%
Dispenza, author of "Breaking
the Habit of Being Yourself,"

00:46:41.780 --> 00:46:44.460 align:middle line:10%
his latest book among
many, many others.

00:46:44.460 --> 00:46:47.110 align:middle line:10%
And we're talking about
how to make new connections

00:46:47.110 --> 00:46:48.650 align:middle line:10%
in the brain, what
it really looks

00:46:48.650 --> 00:46:50.870 align:middle line:10%
like to make those
new connections.

00:46:50.870 --> 00:46:55.300 align:middle line:10%
So let's talk about notable
people, great thinkers,

00:46:55.300 --> 00:46:58.210 align:middle line:10%
people who have made a true mark
or difference in this world.

00:46:58.210 --> 00:46:59.590 align:middle line:90%
What does their brain look like?

00:46:59.590 --> 00:47:02.580 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how did they think
differently than anyone else?

00:47:02.580 --> 00:47:06.810 align:middle line:10%
>>DISPENZA: Well, if you look
at the most commonly fired, most

00:47:06.810 --> 00:47:09.390 align:middle line:10%
neurologically wired set
of thoughts, behaviors,

00:47:09.390 --> 00:47:12.010 align:middle line:10%
and emotions that people
think, that if they

00:47:12.010 --> 00:47:14.480 align:middle line:10%
keep acting the same way,
thinking the same way,

00:47:14.480 --> 00:47:17.900 align:middle line:10%
living the same way, being the
same way, feeling the same way,

00:47:17.900 --> 00:47:21.270 align:middle line:10%
we said that by the time
they're 35 years old,

00:47:21.270 --> 00:47:23.850 align:middle line:10%
they become a very
established identity

00:47:23.850 --> 00:47:26.180 align:middle line:10%
that's a set of
memorized behaviors,

00:47:26.180 --> 00:47:28.880 align:middle line:10%
emotional reactions that
run like automatic programs.

00:47:28.880 --> 00:47:33.170 align:middle line:84%
We could say from a
viewpoint of a brain scan,

00:47:33.170 --> 00:47:36.820 align:middle line:84%
their brain is firing in the
same signature every day.

00:47:36.820 --> 00:47:39.750 align:middle line:84%
We call that signature
a personality.

00:47:39.750 --> 00:47:42.720 align:middle line:84%
Now what makes great
thinkers so unique,

00:47:42.720 --> 00:47:45.340 align:middle line:84%
whether it was Madame
Curie or Joan of Arc

00:47:45.340 --> 00:47:49.600 align:middle line:84%
or Queen Elizabeth I or Mahatma
Gandhi, or Einstein or Tesla--

00:47:49.600 --> 00:47:51.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: They all
had tragic pasts.

00:47:51.310 --> 00:47:52.580 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: They all
had moments where

00:47:52.580 --> 00:47:54.204 align:middle line:84%
they had to overcome
themselves, right?

00:47:54.204 --> 00:47:56.460 align:middle line:90%
And leave their past behind.

00:47:56.460 --> 00:47:58.800 align:middle line:84%
But what they did was
they learned knowledge.

00:47:58.800 --> 00:48:01.420 align:middle line:84%
And as they began to
learn information,

00:48:01.420 --> 00:48:04.360 align:middle line:84%
they begin to contemplate
possibilities.

00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:07.900 align:middle line:84%
They began to ask what I
call frontal lobe questions.

00:48:07.900 --> 00:48:09.520 align:middle line:90%
Open ended questions.

00:48:09.520 --> 00:48:12.360 align:middle line:84%
Questions like, what
would it be like?

00:48:12.360 --> 00:48:13.600 align:middle line:90%
How would it be?

00:48:13.600 --> 00:48:15.020 align:middle line:90%
Speculative questions.

00:48:15.020 --> 00:48:18.710 align:middle line:84%
And as we begin to ask
these speculation questions,

00:48:18.710 --> 00:48:21.060 align:middle line:84%
these open ended
questions, the moment

00:48:21.060 --> 00:48:24.020 align:middle line:84%
we begin to do that, we
begin to make the brain

00:48:24.020 --> 00:48:27.500 align:middle line:84%
work in new patterns and
sequences and combinations.

00:48:27.500 --> 00:48:32.150 align:middle line:84%
And that is what neuroplasticity
is, that kind of ability

00:48:32.150 --> 00:48:33.710 align:middle line:90%
to think outside the box.

00:48:33.710 --> 00:48:35.180 align:middle line:90%
There's no box in your brain.

00:48:35.180 --> 00:48:37.960 align:middle line:84%
But that signature that's
a hardwired pattern

00:48:37.960 --> 00:48:40.110 align:middle line:84%
called an identity
really becomes

00:48:40.110 --> 00:48:43.920 align:middle line:84%
for most people a belief or
a way of looking at life.

00:48:43.920 --> 00:48:47.440 align:middle line:84%
So when we can mix it up
and become so neuralplastic

00:48:47.440 --> 00:48:49.320 align:middle line:84%
and think in new
and unusual ways

00:48:49.320 --> 00:48:52.930 align:middle line:84%
and dare to be original and
step outside of convention,

00:48:52.930 --> 00:48:55.970 align:middle line:84%
step outside of the
common beliefs at the time

00:48:55.970 --> 00:48:58.990 align:middle line:84%
and be bold enough to think
in new and unusual ways,

00:48:58.990 --> 00:49:01.180 align:middle line:84%
and then when you have that
moment of illumination,

00:49:01.180 --> 00:49:03.790 align:middle line:84%
because you create
a new level of mind

00:49:03.790 --> 00:49:06.540 align:middle line:84%
and your brain creates a
hologram or an image of what

00:49:06.540 --> 00:49:11.730 align:middle line:84%
that is, the next step is to
trust that image and say, OK.

00:49:11.730 --> 00:49:13.310 align:middle line:90%
Now let's make it dimensional.

00:49:13.310 --> 00:49:14.590 align:middle line:90%
Let's bring it to life.

00:49:14.590 --> 00:49:17.410 align:middle line:84%
Whether you're inventing
an electric car

00:49:17.410 --> 00:49:19.890 align:middle line:84%
or whether you're
creating relativity

00:49:19.890 --> 00:49:22.260 align:middle line:84%
or you're creating
an x-ray, you have

00:49:22.260 --> 00:49:24.090 align:middle line:84%
to do something
with that vision.

00:49:24.090 --> 00:49:26.020 align:middle line:84%
Because it means
then that potential

00:49:26.020 --> 00:49:28.140 align:middle line:84%
already exists in
the quantum field.

00:49:28.140 --> 00:49:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And what we have to do now
is once we have that mind,

00:49:31.460 --> 00:49:34.156 align:middle line:84%
we have to begin to then
assemble it into reality.

00:49:34.156 --> 00:49:35.780 align:middle line:84%
And this is the plane
of demonstration.

00:49:35.780 --> 00:49:37.072 align:middle line:90%
So we have to bring it to life.

00:49:37.072 --> 00:49:39.155 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So there's a way
of bringing this to life.

00:49:39.155 --> 00:49:40.830 align:middle line:84%
There's a clip
that actually shows

00:49:40.830 --> 00:49:43.032 align:middle line:90%
what neuroplasticity looks like.

00:49:43.032 --> 00:49:43.740 align:middle line:90%
It's fascinating.

00:49:43.740 --> 00:49:44.573 align:middle line:90%
This is fascinating.

00:49:44.573 --> 00:49:46.724 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:49:46.724 --> 00:49:48.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: So let's
just say, you know,

00:49:48.390 --> 00:49:49.860 align:middle line:90%
your brain has all this noise.

00:49:49.860 --> 00:49:53.160 align:middle line:84%
You're thinking about what
you have to do after dinner.

00:49:53.160 --> 00:49:55.210 align:middle line:90%
You have emails to check.

00:49:55.210 --> 00:49:57.700 align:middle line:84%
You have kids to
pick up at ballet.

00:49:57.700 --> 00:50:01.560 align:middle line:90%
You have deadlines at work.

00:50:01.560 --> 00:50:03.990 align:middle line:84%
But you know, you begin
to sit down for a moment

00:50:03.990 --> 00:50:05.460 align:middle line:90%
and you begin to contemplate.

00:50:05.460 --> 00:50:08.672 align:middle line:84%
Now contemplation is really
the assembling process

00:50:08.672 --> 00:50:09.380 align:middle line:90%
in and of itself.

00:50:09.380 --> 00:50:10.990 align:middle line:90%
So you say, what is compassion?

00:50:10.990 --> 00:50:12.500 align:middle line:84%
You have a frontal
lobe question.

00:50:12.500 --> 00:50:14.710 align:middle line:84%
You say, oh, I read
the book on compassion.

00:50:14.710 --> 00:50:17.330 align:middle line:84%
Or I had that experience
with my aunt Mary,

00:50:17.330 --> 00:50:19.045 align:middle line:90%
or I learned about compassion.

00:50:19.045 --> 00:50:20.260 align:middle line:90%
And, oh yeah.

00:50:20.260 --> 00:50:23.620 align:middle line:90%
I saw the DVD.

00:50:23.620 --> 00:50:24.370 align:middle line:90%
And, oh yeah.

00:50:24.370 --> 00:50:25.960 align:middle line:84%
I had that experience
of compassion.

00:50:25.960 --> 00:50:28.970 align:middle line:84%
And, oh boy, do I have a lot
of compassion for myself.

00:50:28.970 --> 00:50:32.080 align:middle line:84%
Your frontal lobe turns on
all these different networks

00:50:32.080 --> 00:50:34.300 align:middle line:84%
and seamlessly
combines them together

00:50:34.300 --> 00:50:35.650 align:middle line:90%
to create a new level of mind.

00:50:35.650 --> 00:50:37.710 align:middle line:84%
And the moment you have
a new level of mind,

00:50:37.710 --> 00:50:40.010 align:middle line:84%
you have a hologram or
an image in your brain

00:50:40.010 --> 00:50:41.760 align:middle line:84%
that represents
what compassion is.

00:50:41.760 --> 00:50:45.590 align:middle line:84%
Now the more you learn, if
you wanted to really know

00:50:45.590 --> 00:50:47.690 align:middle line:84%
about compassion, the
more you learned about it,

00:50:47.690 --> 00:50:49.510 align:middle line:84%
or if you wanted to
learn about success

00:50:49.510 --> 00:50:51.910 align:middle line:84%
or if you wanted to learn
about being a great parent,

00:50:51.910 --> 00:50:55.640 align:middle line:84%
the more you learn from
someone else's experiences

00:50:55.640 --> 00:50:58.020 align:middle line:84%
and you assemble that
information neurologically

00:50:58.020 --> 00:50:59.870 align:middle line:84%
in your brain,
the more you could

00:50:59.870 --> 00:51:01.880 align:middle line:90%
build a more enriched model.

00:51:01.880 --> 00:51:05.610 align:middle line:84%
And then if you could
remind yourself every day,

00:51:05.610 --> 00:51:08.980 align:middle line:84%
which means reproduce
the same level of mind,

00:51:08.980 --> 00:51:12.370 align:middle line:84%
you would begin to install
the hardware in your brain

00:51:12.370 --> 00:51:16.390 align:middle line:84%
to look like the experience
has already happened.

00:51:16.390 --> 00:51:18.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So all of those
books that we read

00:51:18.170 --> 00:51:20.240 align:middle line:84%
and seminars and
transformational movies

00:51:20.240 --> 00:51:22.880 align:middle line:84%
that we see and all
of that does actually

00:51:22.880 --> 00:51:26.416 align:middle line:84%
create-- those were electrical
impulses in the brain firing

00:51:26.416 --> 00:51:27.040 align:middle line:90%
back and forth.

00:51:27.040 --> 00:51:28.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's what makes the
connections happen, right?

00:51:28.670 --> 00:51:30.878 align:middle line:84%
>>DISPENZA: Right, but you
have to ask the questions.

00:51:30.878 --> 00:51:34.020 align:middle line:84%
So you see a book on
transcending culture,

00:51:34.020 --> 00:51:35.870 align:middle line:84%
transcending
beliefs at the time,

00:51:35.870 --> 00:51:38.070 align:middle line:84%
and it motivates you
for a few moments,

00:51:38.070 --> 00:51:41.250 align:middle line:84%
but then you shrink back
into your resting state

00:51:41.250 --> 00:51:42.200 align:middle line:90%
in your life.

00:51:42.200 --> 00:51:45.000 align:middle line:84%
Then I always say, that's
just good dinner conversation.

00:51:45.000 --> 00:51:46.390 align:middle line:90%
Nothing really happened.

00:51:46.390 --> 00:51:48.380 align:middle line:84%
But if you could
become inspired and you

00:51:48.380 --> 00:51:50.860 align:middle line:84%
create a new level of
mind and you say, listen,

00:51:50.860 --> 00:51:52.980 align:middle line:84%
if this person led
a nation and changed

00:51:52.980 --> 00:51:55.300 align:middle line:84%
the beliefs of this
culture, then certainly

00:51:55.300 --> 00:51:57.830 align:middle line:84%
I can change the
beliefs in my workplace.

00:51:57.830 --> 00:52:00.510 align:middle line:84%
Certainly I can change the
beliefs in my community.

00:52:00.510 --> 00:52:02.070 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to be an
individual and I'm

00:52:02.070 --> 00:52:03.740 align:middle line:90%
going to be uncompromising.

00:52:03.740 --> 00:52:06.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to step outside of the
conventional familiar beliefs.

00:52:06.780 --> 00:52:08.540 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to
lead by example.

00:52:08.540 --> 00:52:10.610 align:middle line:84%
Now when you get to that
point where you come out

00:52:10.610 --> 00:52:14.810 align:middle line:84%
of your resting state, you can't
return back to the old self.

00:52:14.810 --> 00:52:18.050 align:middle line:84%
So if you're going to
create a new state of being,

00:52:18.050 --> 00:52:21.530 align:middle line:84%
then it would be a good
idea to remind yourself

00:52:21.530 --> 00:52:23.870 align:middle line:84%
